Yes — this target look is clearer now.

To match that design, the radio should be:

* **24px clickable area**
* **16px visible circle**
* **unselected:** white fill + thin dark border
* **selected:** **green outer circle + white inner dot**
* label aligned vertically with the radio

Use this exact CSS for the radio section and **remove any older radio rules**:

```css
.sales-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
    margin: 0 0 40px;
}

.sales-option {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;

    font-family: 'Open Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 24px;
    color: #000000;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.sales-option input[type='radio'] {
    appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;

    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    flex: 0 0 24px;
    margin: 0;

    border: 0;
    background: transparent;
    position: relative;
    cursor: pointer;
}

/* visible radio circle */
.sales-option input[type='radio']::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);

    width: 16px;
    height: 16px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    box-sizing: border-box;

    background-color: #ffffff;
    border: 1.5px solid #1f2a2a;
}

/* selected state */
.sales-option input[type='radio']:checked::before {
    background-color: #6BDD00;
    border: 1.5px solid #154734;
}

/* white inner dot */
.sales-option input[type='radio']:checked::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);

    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: #ffffff;
}

.sales-option input[type='radio']:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid #6BDD00;
    outline-offset: 2px;
    border-radius: 50%;
}

.sales-option span {
    font: inherit;
    color: #000000;
}
```

## Why this will look closer

Your current radio looks too large because the **whole 24px area** is being drawn as the circle.

This version keeps:

* `24px` for accessibility/click area
* only `16px` as the visible radio
* a small centered white dot
* tighter spacing like the design

